<h1 data-start="356" data-end="400">1. Survival Analysis by Stage at Diagnosis</h1>
<h3 data-start="402" data-end="418">Project idea</h3>
<p data-start="419" data-end="514"><strong data-start="419" data-end="514">Does stage at diagnosis affect overall survival in patients with lung or colorectal cancer?</strong></p>
<h3 data-start="516" data-end="538">Why this is strong</h3>
<p data-start="539" data-end="641">This is one of the most classic and recognizable oncology biostatistics projects. It shows you can do:</p>
<ul data-start="642" data-end="757">
<li data-start="642" data-end="663">
<p data-start="644" data-end="663">Kaplan–Meier curves</p>
</li>
<li data-start="664" data-end="680">
<p data-start="666" data-end="680">log-rank tests</p>
</li>
<li data-start="681" data-end="714">
<p data-start="683" data-end="714">Cox proportional hazards models</p>
</li>
<li data-start="715" data-end="757">
<p data-start="717" data-end="757">clinical interpretation of hazard ratios</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="759" data-end="775">Skills shown</h3>
<ul data-start="776" data-end="855">
<li data-start="776" data-end="795">
<p data-start="778" data-end="795">survival analysis</p>
</li>
<li data-start="796" data-end="807">
<p data-start="798" data-end="807">censoring</p>
</li>
<li data-start="808" data-end="832">
<p data-start="810" data-end="832">time-to-event modeling</p>
</li>
<li data-start="833" data-end="855">
<p data-start="835" data-end="855">covariate adjustment</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="857" data-end="883">Portfolio deliverables</h3>
<ul data-start="884" data-end="970">
<li data-start="884" data-end="901">
<p data-start="886" data-end="901">survival curves</p>
</li>
<li data-start="902" data-end="919">
<p data-start="904" data-end="919">Cox model table</p>
</li>
<li data-start="920" data-end="950">
<p data-start="922" data-end="950">short written interpretation</p>
</li>
<li data-start="951" data-end="970">
<p data-start="953" data-end="970">assumptions check</p>
</li>
</ul>
