ode-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span class="ͼ6"># 1. Load packages</span><br><span class="ͼe">library</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">tidyverse</span><span>)</span><br><span class="ͼe">library</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">survival</span><span>)</span><br><span class="ͼe">library</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">survminer</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 2. Import data</span><br><span class="ͼe">df</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">read.csv</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼc">"oncology_survival_data.csv"</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 3. Clean data</span><br><span class="ͼe">df</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">%&gt;%</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">mutate</span><span>(</span><br><span>    </span><span class="ͼe">stage</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">factor</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">stage</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">levels</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">c</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼc">"I"</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼc">"II"</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼc">"III"</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼc">"IV"</span><span>)),</span><br><span>    </span><span class="ͼe">status</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">ifelse</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">status</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">==</span><span> </span><span class="ͼc">"Dead"</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼb">1</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼb">0</span><span>)</span><br><span>  ) </span><span class="ͼe">%&gt;%</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">drop_na</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">survival_months</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">status</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">stage</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">age</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">sex</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 4. Kaplan-Meier model</span><br><span class="ͼe">km_fit</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">survfit</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">Surv</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">survival_months</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">status</span><span>) </span><span class="ͼ8">~</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">stage</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">data</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 5. Plot KM curve</span><br><span class="ͼe">ggsurvplot</span><span>(</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">km_fit</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">data</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">pval</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">TRUE</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">risk.table</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">TRUE</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">conf.int</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">TRUE</span><br><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 6. Cox proportional hazards model</span><br><span class="ͼe">cox_fit</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">coxph</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">Surv</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">survival_months</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">status</span><span>) </span><span class="ͼ8">~</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">stage</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">+</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">age</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">+</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">sex</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">data</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span>)</span><br><span class="ͼe">summary</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">cox_fit</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 7. Check proportional hazards assumption</span><br><span class="ͼe">cox.zph</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">cox_fit</span><span>)</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
