<hr data-start="2162" data-end="2165">
<h1 data-start="2167" data-end="2231">2. Logistic Regression for Metastasis or Lymph Node Positivity</h1>
<h3 data-start="2233" data-end="2249">Project idea</h3>
<p data-start="2250" data-end="2352"><strong data-start="2250" data-end="2352">Which clinical factors predict lymph node metastasis in breast, colorectal, or endometrial cancer?</strong></p>
<h3 data-start="2354" data-end="2376">Why this is strong</h3>
<p data-start="2377" data-end="2485">Very practical and clinically meaningful. It shows you can handle binary outcomes and interpret odds ratios.</p>
<h3 data-start="2487" data-end="2503">Skills shown</h3>
<ul data-start="2504" data-end="2618">
<li data-start="2504" data-end="2525">
<p data-start="2506" data-end="2525">logistic regression</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2526" data-end="2539">
<p data-start="2528" data-end="2539">odds ratios</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2540" data-end="2557">
<p data-start="2542" data-end="2557">variable coding</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2558" data-end="2577">
<p data-start="2560" data-end="2577">model diagnostics</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2578" data-end="2618">
<p data-start="2580" data-end="2618">ROC curve / classification performance</p>
</li>
</ul>
