<h1 data-start="5290" data-end="5327">4. Cancer Registry Trends Over Time</h1>
<h3 data-start="5329" data-end="5345">Project idea</h3>
<p data-start="5346" data-end="5459"><strong data-start="5346" data-end="5459">Have incidence patterns, stage at diagnosis, or treatment utilization changed over time in a specific cancer?</strong></p>
<p data-start="5461" data-end="5569">This one fits your background especially well because registry-style analysis is already in your wheelhouse.</p>
<h3 data-start="5571" data-end="5593">Why this is strong</h3>
<p data-start="5594" data-end="5699">This project shows you can work with larger real-world oncology datasets and ask epidemiologic questions.</p>
<h3 data-start="5701" data-end="5717">Skills shown</h3>
<ul data-start="5718" data-end="5850">
<li data-start="5718" data-end="5745">
<p data-start="5720" data-end="5745">descriptive biostatistics</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5746" data-end="5762">
<p data-start="5748" data-end="5762">trend analysis</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5763" data-end="5782">
<p data-start="5765" data-end="5782">grouped summaries</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5783" data-end="5798">
<p data-start="5785" data-end="5798">visualization</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5799" data-end="5850">
<p data-start="5801" data-end="5850">interpretation for population-level oncology data</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="5852" data-end="5870">Good questions</h3>
<ul data-start="5871" data-end="6027">
<li data-start="5871" data-end="5927">
<p data-start="5873" data-end="5927">Has early-onset colorectal cancer increased over time?</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5928" data-end="5971">
<p data-start="5930" data-end="5971">Has stage IV diagnosis changed over time?</p>
</li>
<li data-start="5972" data-end="6027">
<p data-start="5974" data-end="6027">Are there treatment differences by demographic group?</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="6029" data-end="6052">Suggested repo name</h3>
<p data-start="6053" data-end="6090"><code data-start="6053" data-end="6090">04-oncology-registry-trend-analysis</code></p>
<h3 data-start="6092" data-end="6112">R code structure</h3>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="6113" data-end="6778"><div class="relative w-full my-4"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-eri7ssmm.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>R</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-eri7ssmm.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span class="ͼ6"># 1. Load packages</span><br><span class="ͼe">library</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">tidyverse</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 2. Import data</span><br><span class="ͼe">df</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">read.csv</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼc">"registry_data.csv"</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 3. Clean data</span><br><span class="ͼe">df</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">%&gt;%</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">mutate</span><span>(</span><br><span>    </span><span class="ͼe">year</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">as.integer</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">year</span><span>),</span><br><span>    </span><span class="ͼe">age_group</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">case_when</span><span>(</span><br><span>      </span><span class="ͼe">age</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">50</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">~</span><span> </span><span class="ͼc">"&lt;50"</span><span>,</span><br><span>      </span><span class="ͼe">age</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&gt;=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">50</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&amp;</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">age</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">65</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">~</span><span> </span><span class="ͼc">"50-64"</span><span>,</span><br><span>      </span><span class="ͼe">age</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&gt;=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">65</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">~</span><span> </span><span class="ͼc">"65+"</span><br><span>    ),</span><br><span>    </span><span class="ͼe">stage</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">factor</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">stage</span><span>)</span><br><span>  )</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 4. Summarize trends</span><br><span class="ͼe">trend_df</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">%&gt;%</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">group_by</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">year</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">age_group</span><span>) </span><span class="ͼe">%&gt;%</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">summarise</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">cases</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">n</span><span>(), </span><span class="ͼe">.groups</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼc">"drop"</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 5. Plot</span><br><span class="ͼe">ggplot</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">trend_df</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">aes</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">x</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">year</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">y</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">cases</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">color</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">age_group</span><span>)) </span><span class="ͼ8">+</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">geom_line</span><span>() </span><span class="ͼ8">+</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">geom_point</span><span>() </span><span class="ͼ8">+</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">theme_minimal</span><span>()</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 6. Optional regression trend test</span><br><span class="ͼe">fit</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">lm</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">cases</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">~</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">year</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">+</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">age_group</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">data</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">trend_df</span><span>)</span><br><span class="ͼe">summary</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">fit</span><span>)</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<h3 data-start="6780" data-end="6804">Great write-up angle</h3>
<p data-start="6805" data-end="7011">Because you know oncology data 
definitions, you can explain why shifts in stage, age, or treatment 
patterns matter clinically — that’s a big advantage over someone doing 
statistics without oncology context.</p>
<hr data-start="7013" data-end="7016">
<h1 data-start="7018" data-end="7061">5. Biomarker or Genomic Predictor Project</h1>
<h3 data-start="7063" data-end="7079">Project idea</h3>
<p data-start="7080" data-end="7170"><strong data-start="7080" data-end="7170">Is biomarker status or gene expression associated with survival or treatment response?</strong></p>
<h3 data-start="7172" data-end="7194">Why this is strong</h3>
<p data-start="7195" data-end="7329">This directly connects your <strong data-start="7223" data-end="7258">precision medicine and genomics</strong> background to biostatistics. It makes your portfolio feel specialized.</p>
<h3 data-start="7331" data-end="7347">Skills shown</h3>
<ul data-start="7348" data-end="7452">
<li data-start="7348" data-end="7368">
<p data-start="7350" data-end="7368">biomarker analysis</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7369" data-end="7399">
<p data-start="7371" data-end="7399">grouped survival comparisons</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7400" data-end="7421">
<p data-start="7402" data-end="7421">regression modeling</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7422" data-end="7452">
<p data-start="7424" data-end="7452">translational interpretation</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="7454" data-end="7466">Examples</h3>
<ul data-start="7467" data-end="7646">
<li data-start="7467" data-end="7538">
<p data-start="7469" data-end="7538">Does biomarker-positive vs biomarker-negative status affect survival?</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7539" data-end="7595">
<p data-start="7541" data-end="7595">Is mutation status associated with treatment response?</p>
</li>
<li data-start="7596" data-end="7646">
<p data-start="7598" data-end="7646">Are expression groups associated with prognosis?</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="7648" data-end="7671">Suggested repo name</h3>
<p data-start="7672" data-end="7703"><code data-start="7672" data-end="7703">05-biomarker-outcome-analysis</code></p>
<h3 data-start="7705" data-end="7725">R code structure</h3>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="7726" data-end="8409"><div class="relative w-full my-4"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-eri7ssmm.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>R</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-eri7ssmm.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span class="ͼ6"># 1. Load packages</span><br><span class="ͼe">library</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">tidyverse</span><span>)</span><br><span class="ͼe">library</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">survival</span><span>)</span><br><span class="ͼe">library</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">survminer</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 2. Import data</span><br><span class="ͼe">df</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">read.csv</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼc">"biomarker_data.csv"</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 3. Clean data</span><br><span class="ͼe">df</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">%&gt;%</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">mutate</span><span>(</span><br><span>    </span><span class="ͼe">biomarker_group</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">factor</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">biomarker_group</span><span>),</span><br><span>    </span><span class="ͼe">status</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">ifelse</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">status</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">==</span><span> </span><span class="ͼc">"Dead"</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼb">1</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼb">0</span><span>)</span><br><span>  ) </span><span class="ͼe">%&gt;%</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">drop_na</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">survival_months</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">status</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">biomarker_group</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 4. Kaplan-Meier by biomarker</span><br><span class="ͼe">km_fit</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">survfit</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">Surv</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">survival_months</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">status</span><span>) </span><span class="ͼ8">~</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">biomarker_group</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">data</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼe">ggsurvplot</span><span>(</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">km_fit</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">data</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">pval</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">TRUE</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">risk.table</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">TRUE</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">conf.int</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">TRUE</span><br><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 5. Adjusted Cox model</span><br><span class="ͼe">cox_fit</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">coxph</span><span>(</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">Surv</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">survival_months</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">status</span><span>) </span><span class="ͼ8">~</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">biomarker_group</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">+</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">age</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">+</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">stage</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">+</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">treatment</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">data</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><br><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼe">summary</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">cox_fit</span><span>)</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<h3 data-start="8411" data-end="8449">Why hiring managers will like this</h3>
<p data-start="8450" data-end="8502">It signals that you can work at the intersection of:</p>
<ul data-start="8503" data-end="8565">
<li data-start="8503" data-end="8513">
<p data-start="8505" data-end="8513">oncology</p>
</li>
<li data-start="8514" data-end="8524">
<p data-start="8516" data-end="8524">genomics</p>
</li>
<li data-start="8525" data-end="8544">
<p data-start="8527" data-end="8544">outcomes research</p>
</li>
<li data-start="8545" data-end="8565">
<p data-start="8547" data-end="8565">applied statistics</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="8567" data-end="8598">That’s a very marketable niche.</p>
<hr data-start="8600" data-end="8603">
<h1 data-start="8605" data-end="8631">Best order to build them</h1>
<p data-start="8633" data-end="8668">For you, I’d do them in this order:</p>
<h3 data-start="8670" data-end="8703">1. Survival analysis by stage</h3>
<p data-start="8704" data-end="8753">Best first project. Very standard and impressive.</p>
<h3 data-start="8755" data-end="8801">2. Logistic regression for metastasis risk</h3>
<p data-start="8802" data-end="8842">Builds regression interpretation skills.</p>
<h3 data-start="8844" data-end="8874">3. Registry trend analysis</h3>
<p data-start="8875" data-end="8911">Lets your oncology background shine.</p>
<h3 data-start="8913" data-end="8950">4. Treatment interaction analysis</h3>
<p data-start="8951" data-end="8995">Good bridge from coursework to applied work.</p>
<h3 data-start="8997" data-end="9029">5. Biomarker/genomic project</h3>
<p data-start="9030" data-end="9082">Most specialized; great once the first few are done.</p>
<hr data-start="9084" data-end="9087">
<h1 data-start="9089" data-end="9130">Ideal GitHub structure for each project</h1>
<p data-start="9132" data-end="9169">Use the same clean layout every time:</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="9171" data-end="9341"><div class="relative w-full my-4"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-eri7ssmm.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>R</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-eri7ssmm.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span class="ͼe">project</span><span class="ͼ8">-</span><span class="ͼe">name</span><span class="ͼ8">/</span><br><span>│</span><br><span>├── </span><span class="ͼe">data</span><span class="ͼ8">/</span><br><span>│   └── </span><span class="ͼe">raw_data.csv</span><br><span>├── </span><span class="ͼe">scripts</span><span class="ͼ8">/</span><br><span>│   └── </span><span class="ͼe">analysis.R</span><br><span>├── </span><span class="ͼe">output</span><span class="ͼ8">/</span><br><span>│   ├── </span><span class="ͼe">tables</span><span class="ͼ8">/</span><br><span>│   └── </span><span class="ͼe">figures</span><span class="ͼ8">/</span><br><span>├── </span><span class="ͼe">README.md</span><br><span>└── </span><span class="ͼe">project_summary.pdf</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="9343" data-end="9346">
<h1 data-start="9348" data-end="9381">What to include in every README</h1>
<p data-start="9383" data-end="9422">Keep each README simple and consistent:</p>
<h3 data-start="9424" data-end="9436">Sections</h3>
<ul data-start="9437" data-end="9541">
<li data-start="9437" data-end="9444">
<p data-start="9439" data-end="9444">Title</p>
</li>
<li data-start="9445" data-end="9464">
<p data-start="9447" data-end="9464">Clinical question</p>
</li>
<li data-start="9465" data-end="9474">
<p data-start="9467" data-end="9474">Dataset</p>
</li>
<li data-start="9475" data-end="9484">
<p data-start="9477" data-end="9484">Methods</p>
</li>
<li data-start="9485" data-end="9499">
<p data-start="9487" data-end="9499">Key findings</p>
</li>
<li data-start="9500" data-end="9515">
<p data-start="9502" data-end="9515">Files in repo</p>
</li>
<li data-start="9516" data-end="9541">
<p data-start="9518" data-end="9541">How to run the analysis</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="9543" data-end="9563">Example headings</h3>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="9564" data-end="10095"><div class="relative w-full my-4"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-eri7ssmm.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>Markdown</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-eri7ssmm.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span># Survival Analysis of Lung Cancer by Stage</span><br><br><span>## Clinical Question</span><br><span>Does stage at diagnosis affect overall survival?</span><br><br><span>## Dataset</span><br><span>This project uses a de-identified oncology dataset containing survival time, stage, age, sex, and treatment variables.</span><br><br><span>## Methods</span><br><span>- Kaplan-Meier survival curves</span><br><span>- Log-rank test</span><br><span>- Cox proportional hazards model</span><br><br><span>## Key Findings</span><br><span>Later stage at diagnosis was associated with worse overall survival.</span><br><br><span>## Files</span><br><span>- scripts/analysis.R</span><br><span>- output/figures/km_plot.png</span><br><span>- output/tables/cox_results.csv</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="10097" data-end="10100">
<h1 data-start="10102" data-end="10144">What hiring managers usually want to see</h1>
<p data-start="10146" data-end="10243">They do <strong data-start="10154" data-end="10161">not</strong> need your portfolio to be insanely advanced. They mostly want proof that you can:</p>
<ul data-start="10245" data-end="10370">
<li data-start="10245" data-end="10257">
<p data-start="10247" data-end="10257">clean data</p>
</li>
<li data-start="10258" data-end="10288">
<p data-start="10260" data-end="10288">choose an appropriate method</p>
</li>
<li data-start="10289" data-end="10309">
<p data-start="10291" data-end="10309">run the model in R</p>
</li>
<li data-start="10310" data-end="10339">
<p data-start="10312" data-end="10339">interpret results correctly</p>
</li>
<li data-start="10340" data-end="10370">
<p data-start="10342" data-end="10370">communicate findings clearly</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="10372" data-end="10535">That’s where your oncology 
background gives you a real edge, because you can explain results in a 
way that feels clinically meaningful instead of purely technical.</p>
<hr data-start="10537" data-end="10540">
