<h1 data-start="2749" data-end="2772">Full starter R script</h1>
<p data-start="2774" data-end="2824">Here’s a strong starter script you can build from.</p>
<pre class="overflow-visible! px-0!" data-start="2826" data-end="4654"><div class="relative w-full my-4"><div class=""><div class="relative"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0"><div class="h-full min-h-0 min-w-0" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"><div class="border border-token-border-light border-radius-3xl corner-superellipse/1.1 rounded-3xl"><div class="h-full w-full border-radius-3xl bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary corner-superellipse/1.1 overflow-clip rounded-3xl lxnfua_clipPathFallback"><div class="sticky z-2 select-none top-(--sticky-padding-top)"><div class="flex w-full items-center justify-between py-1.5 ps-4 pe-1.5 font-sans md:ps-5 bg-token-bg-elevated-secondary"><div class="flex max-w-[75%] min-w-0 cursor-default items-center text-sm font-medium justify-self-start text-token-text-primary"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-sm me-2.5 shrink-0"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-eri7ssmm.svg#e45ab3" fill="currentColor"></use></svg>R</div><div class="flex flex-row items-center gap-0.5 justify-self-end"><button class="flex gap-1 items-center select-none py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/10 size-9 rounded-full px-2" aria-label="Copy" data-state="closed"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" aria-hidden="true" class="icon-md"><use href="/cdn/assets/sprites-core-eri7ssmm.svg#ce3544" fill="currentColor"></use></svg></button></div></div></div><div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-4 top-12 bottom-4"><div class="pointer-events-none sticky z-40 shrink-0 z-1!" style="top: calc(calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px) - 1px * 3); margin-bottom: calc(-4px); height: calc(4px); mask-image: linear-gradient(transparent 25%, white 75%);"><div class="sticky bg-token-border-light" style="top: calc(var(--sticky-padding-top) + 48px); height: 1px;"></div></div></div><div class="" style="transform: none;"><div class="relative z-0 flex max-w-full"><div id="code-block-viewer" dir="ltr" class="q9tKkq_viewer cm-editor z-10 light:cm-light dark:cm-light flex h-full w-full flex-col items-stretch ͼ5 ͼj"><div class="cm-scroller"><div class="cm-content q9tKkq_readonly"><span class="ͼ6"># ==========================================</span><br><span class="ͼ6"># Survival Analysis by Stage at Diagnosis</span><br><span class="ͼ6"># Lung Cancer Project</span><br><span class="ͼ6"># ==========================================</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 1. Load packages</span><br><span class="ͼe">library</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">tidyverse</span><span>)</span><br><span class="ͼe">library</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">survival</span><span>)</span><br><span class="ͼe">library</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">survminer</span><span>)</span><br><span class="ͼe">library</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">broom</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 2. Import data</span><br><span class="ͼe">df</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">read.csv</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼc">"data/lung_cancer_survival.csv"</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 3. Inspect data</span><br><span class="ͼe">str</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span>)</span><br><span class="ͼe">summary</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 4. Clean and prepare variables</span><br><span class="ͼe">df</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">%&gt;%</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">mutate</span><span>(</span><br><span>    </span><span class="ͼe">stage</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">factor</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">stage</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">levels</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">c</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼc">"I"</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼc">"II"</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼc">"III"</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼc">"IV"</span><span>)),</span><br><span>    </span><span class="ͼe">sex</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">factor</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">sex</span><span>),</span><br><span>    </span><span class="ͼe">status</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">as.numeric</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">status</span><span>)</span><br><span>  ) </span><span class="ͼe">%&gt;%</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">drop_na</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">survival_months</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">status</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">stage</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">age</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">sex</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 5. Check sample size by stage</span><br><span class="ͼe">table</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span class="ͼ8">$</span><span class="ͼe">stage</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 6. Create survival object</span><br><span class="ͼe">surv_obj</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">Surv</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">time</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span class="ͼ8">$</span><span class="ͼe">survival_months</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">event</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span class="ͼ8">$</span><span class="ͼe">status</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 7. Kaplan-Meier survival analysis by stage</span><br><span class="ͼe">km_fit</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">survfit</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">surv_obj</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">~</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">stage</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">data</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 8. Plot Kaplan-Meier curves</span><br><span class="ͼe">km_plot</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">ggsurvplot</span><span>(</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">km_fit</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">data</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">pval</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">TRUE</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">conf.int</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">TRUE</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">risk.table</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">TRUE</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">xlab</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼc">"Survival Time (Months)"</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">ylab</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼc">"Overall Survival Probability"</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">title</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼc">"Kaplan-Meier Survival Curves by Stage at Diagnosis"</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">legend.title</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼc">"Stage"</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">legend.labs</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">c</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼc">"Stage I"</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼc">"Stage II"</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼc">"Stage III"</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼc">"Stage IV"</span><span>)</span><br><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼe">print</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">km_plot</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 9. Log-rank test</span><br><span class="ͼe">logrank_test</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">survdiff</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">surv_obj</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">~</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">stage</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">data</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span>)</span><br><span class="ͼe">logrank_test</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 10. Cox proportional hazards model</span><br><span class="ͼe">cox_fit</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">coxph</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">surv_obj</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">~</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">stage</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">+</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">age</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">+</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">sex</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">data</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">df</span><span>)</span><br><span class="ͼe">summary</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">cox_fit</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 11. Hazard ratios with confidence intervals</span><br><span class="ͼe">cox_results</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">tidy</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">cox_fit</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">exponentiate</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">TRUE</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">conf.int</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">TRUE</span><span>)</span><br><span class="ͼe">cox_results</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 12. Check proportional hazards assumption</span><br><span class="ͼe">ph_test</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">&lt;-</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">cox.zph</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">cox_fit</span><span>)</span><br><span class="ͼe">ph_test</span><br><span class="ͼe">plot</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">ph_test</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼ6"># 13. Save results</span><br><span class="ͼe">write.csv</span><span>(</span><span class="ͼe">cox_results</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼc">"output/tables/cox_results.csv"</span><span>, </span><span class="ͼe">row.names</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">FALSE</span><span>)</span><br><br><span class="ͼe">ggsave</span><span>(</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">filename</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼc">"output/figures/km_plot.png"</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">plot</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼe">km_plot</span><span class="ͼ8">$</span><span class="ͼe">plot</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">width</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">8</span><span>,</span><br><span>  </span><span class="ͼe">height</span><span> </span><span class="ͼ8">=</span><span> </span><span class="ͼb">6</span><br><span>)</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class=""><div class="" style="width: 100%; transform: none;"></div></div></div></div></div></pre>
<hr data-start="4656" data-end="4659">
<h1 data-start="4661" data-end="4686">What each part is doing</h1>
<h2 data-start="4688" data-end="4710">Kaplan–Meier curves</h2>
<p data-start="4711" data-end="4765">These let you visually compare survival across stages.</p>
<p data-start="4767" data-end="4793">What you’ll likely expect:</p>
<ul data-start="4794" data-end="4847">
<li data-start="4794" data-end="4820">
<p data-start="4796" data-end="4820">Stage I highest survival</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4821" data-end="4847">
<p data-start="4823" data-end="4847">Stage IV lowest survival</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-start="4849" data-end="4865">Log-rank test</h2>
<p data-start="4866" data-end="4947">This tests whether the survival curves are significantly different across groups.</p>
<h2 data-start="4949" data-end="4982">Cox proportional hazards model</h2>
<p data-start="4983" data-end="5078">This estimates how much stage affects the <strong data-start="5025" data-end="5044">hazard of death</strong>, while adjusting for age and sex.</p>
<p data-start="5080" data-end="5103">Example interpretation:</p>
<ul data-start="5104" data-end="5280">
<li data-start="5104" data-end="5280">
<p data-start="5106" data-end="5280">If Stage IV has HR = 3.20 compared with Stage I, then patients diagnosed at Stage IV have <strong data-start="5196" data-end="5229">3.2 times the hazard of death</strong> relative to Stage I, holding age and sex constant.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="5282" data-end="5285">
<h1 data-start="5287" data-end="5322">Example results write-up template</h1>
<p data-start="5324" data-end="5371">You can use this later once you run your model:</p>
<blockquote data-start="5373" data-end="5999">
<p data-start="5375" data-end="5999">Kaplan–Meier survival analysis 
showed clear differences in overall survival by stage at diagnosis. 
Patients diagnosed with earlier-stage lung cancer had higher survival 
probabilities over time, while patients diagnosed with later-stage 
disease had poorer survival outcomes. The log-rank test indicated that 
survival differed significantly across stage groups. In the Cox 
proportional hazards model adjusted for age and sex, later stage at 
diagnosis was associated with an increased hazard of death compared with
 Stage I, supporting the clinical expectation that advanced disease at 
presentation is linked to worse prognosis.</p>
</blockquote>
