<h1 data-start="3737" data-end="3786">8️⃣ Why This Is a Great First Portfolio Project</h1>
<p data-start="3788" data-end="3881">This single analysis demonstrates the <strong data-start="3826" data-end="3880">core statistical methods used in oncology research</strong>:</p>
<ul data-start="3883" data-end="3943">
<li data-start="3883" data-end="3902">
<p data-start="3885" data-end="3902">Survival analysis</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3903" data-end="3918">
<p data-start="3905" data-end="3918">Hazard ratios</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3919" data-end="3943">
<p data-start="3921" data-end="3943">Time-to-event modeling</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="3945" data-end="3963">These are used in:</p>
<ul data-start="3965" data-end="4059">
<li data-start="3965" data-end="3982">
<p data-start="3967" data-end="3982">clinical trials</p>
</li>
<li data-start="3983" data-end="4004">
<p data-start="3985" data-end="4004">cancer epidemiology</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4005" data-end="4038">
<p data-start="4007" data-end="4038">treatment effectiveness studies</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4039" data-end="4059">
<p data-start="4041" data-end="4059">biomarker research</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start="4061" data-end="4064">
<h1 data-start="4066" data-end="4126">9️⃣ What I Recommend for Your <strong data-start="4098" data-end="4126">Second Portfolio Project</strong></h1>
<p data-start="4128" data-end="4172">Using this same dataset you could easily do:</p>
<p data-start="4174" data-end="4187"><strong data-start="4174" data-end="4187">Project 2</strong></p>
<h3 data-start="4189" data-end="4232">Smoking Status and Lung Cancer Survival</h3>
<p data-start="4234" data-end="4252">Research question:</p>
<blockquote data-start="4254" data-end="4328">
<p data-start="4256" data-end="4328">Does smoking status affect survival outcomes among lung cancer patients?</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="4330" data-end="4338">Methods:</p>
<ul data-start="4340" data-end="4405">
<li data-start="4340" data-end="4361">
<p data-start="4342" data-end="4361">Kaplan–Meier curves</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4362" data-end="4373">
<p data-start="4364" data-end="4373">Cox model</p>
</li>
<li data-start="4374" data-end="4405">
<p data-start="4376" data-end="4405">adjust for age, stage, gender</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="4407" data-end="4472">That would show you can analyze <strong data-start="4439" data-end="4455">risk factors</strong>, not just stage.</p>
<hr data-start="4474" data-end="4477">
