<p data-start="2684" data-end="2730">Which is <strong data-start="2693" data-end="2729">exactly what biostatisticians do</strong>.</p>
<hr data-start="2732" data-end="2735">
<h1 data-start="2737" data-end="2767">Good news about your project</h1>
<p data-start="2768" data-end="2892">Because your dataset includes <strong data-start="2798" data-end="2825">many oncology variables</strong>, you can easily build <strong data-start="2848" data-end="2869">multiple projects</strong> from the same dataset:</p>
<p data-start="2894" data-end="3070">1️⃣ Survival by stage<br data-start="2915" data-end="2918">
2️⃣ Smoking status vs survival<br data-start="2948" data-end="2951">
3️⃣ Predicting metastasis (logistic regression)<br data-start="2998" data-end="3001">
4️⃣ Tumor size vs survival<br data-start="3027" data-end="3030">
