<p data-start="224" data-end="262">I'll walk you through the easiest way.</p>
<hr data-start="264" data-end="267">
<h1 data-start="269" data-end="295">Step 1: Exit this screen</h1>
<p data-start="296" data-end="333">Click <strong data-start="302" data-end="320">Cancel changes</strong> (top right).</p>
<p data-start="335" data-end="386">That will take you back to the repository homepage.</p>
<hr data-start="388" data-end="391">
<h1 data-start="393" data-end="423">Step 2: Upload files instead</h1>
<p data-start="424" data-end="434">Now click:</p>
<p data-start="436" data-end="463"><strong data-start="436" data-end="463">Add file → Upload files</strong></p>
<p data-start="465" data-end="512">You should see a page that says something like:</p>
<blockquote data-start="514" data-end="541">
<p data-start="516" data-end="541">Drag files here to upload</p>
</blockquote>
<p data-start="543" data-end="545">or</p>
<blockquote data-start="547" data-end="566">
<p data-start="549" data-end="566">Choose your files</p>
</blockquote>
<hr data-start="568" data-end="571">
<h1 data-start="573" data-end="605">Step 3: Find your files from R</h1>
<p data-start="607" data-end="668">Your files exist <strong data-start="624" data-end="644">on your computer</strong>, not inside GitHub yet.</p>
<p data-start="670" data-end="715">In <strong data-start="673" data-end="684">RStudio</strong>, go to the bottom right panel:</p>
<p data-start="717" data-end="730"><strong data-start="717" data-end="730">Files tab</strong></p>
<p data-start="732" data-end="771">Navigate to where your files are saved.</p>
<p data-start="773" data-end="804">You likely have something like:</p>
